6. Supports, Comments, Reflections
- Thinking of scrapping the two different IDPs, is it possible to have 1 type where clubs can add different features of the IDP based on their needs and club type, ie, grassroots compared to academies might want different features. I'm also thinking the features for IDP could be different based on pricing plans or subscription tiers in the future. 

Club methodology
- Editable for club/admin
- Ability to add sections to the club methodology within each section/heading to further personalise
- 'Player profiles' section for clubs to define positional profiles for players, roles and responsibilities for each, what type of player clubs want to develop or coach . This section would be additional to 'Academy Identity', 'Game Model', 'Development Frameworks', 'Alignment Tags'. 
- Option to print Club methodology as a PDF? (just a thought, not super important)

Session Planning & Periodisation
- Able to view as calendar form for coaches 
- Option to upload PDF documents to individual sessions
- More connection between club/admin account and coaches accounts, when club creates plan, they both can see and edit same thing
- Ability to allow more autonomy for coaches based on clubs needs, ie, grassroots clubs might give coaches more autonomy to create multi week plans and season long plans where as some organisations with take complete control of session structure, training topics, training blocks and season plans